AngloGold, Harmony, Massmart May Be Active: South African Equities Preview

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-03-24T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/anglogold-harmony-massmart-may-be-active-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index gained for a
third day, rising 432.14, or 1.4 percent, to 31,647.69 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  : Gold futures jumped to a
record of $1,448.60 an ounce as turmoil in Libya, Japan and
 Europe  spurred demand for the precious metal as an alternative
investment. Africa’s largest miner of the metal rose 7.01 rand,
or 2.2 percent, to 326 rand. Harmony Gold Mining Co. Ltd. (HAR
SJ), which  RBC Capital Markets  said is a potential takeover
target, climbed 10.45 rand, or 12 percent, to 98.40 rand.  Massmart Holdings Ltd. (MSM)  : The Competition Tribunal
has scheduled a procedural hearing today to allow arguments
related to government’s request for further information
regarding Wal-Mart Stores Inc.’s proposed acquisition of 51
percent of Massmart. Massmart shares advanced 50 cents, or 0.4
percent, to 132.50 rand.  Sovereign Food Investments (SOV)  Ltd: The holding
company of a poultry business said it used 150 million rand ($21
million) from its rights offer to repay interest-bearing debt,
which should result in an additional cash flow saving of about 4
million rand per month. Sovereign added 5 cents, or 0.9 percent,
to 5.80 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Bonorchis in Johannesburg at 
 rbonorchis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
